analysis: The documents all pertain to exemptions from compulsory retirement for government employees. They cite the same legal authority (section 204 of the act of June 30, 1932) and follow a similar structure, starting with 'Whereas, in my judgment, the public interest requires that...' and then stating the exemption. The exemptions are for various positions across different departments.
tags: section 204 of the act of June 30, 1932
title: Government Employee Retirement Exemptions
